religion /rɪˈlɪdʒən/

(religions) 

1. N-UNCOUNT Religion is belief in a god or gods and the activities that are connected with this belief, such as praying or worshipping in a building such as a church or temple. 宗教 

例： ...his understanding of Indian philosophy and religion. …他对于印度哲学和宗教的理解。 

2. N-COUNT A religion is a particular system of belief in a god or gods and the activities that are connected with this system. (一种) 宗教 

例： ...the Christian religion. …基督教。

</div>

